10. We have different types of DI

Setter DI
Contructor DI

Difference between setter and constructor injection

1.It is a type of dependency  injection  where setter method is used to inject dependencies.

It is a type of dependency  injection  where constructor is used to inject dependencies.

2.property tag is used to inject dependencies.

constructor-arg tag is used to inject dependencies.

3.If any dependency is not injected by the user then that dependency is injected by the spring container implicitly with default values.

User should inject all dependency explicitly.

4.It is not mandatory to maintain the order while injecting dependencies.

It is mandatory to maintain the order while injecting dependencies.

